# Patterns & Mistakes

> Record rules learned from mistakes here. These prevent the same error across sessions.
>
> Format: Rule title → When it applies → What went wrong → The rule going forward.
> When a pattern saves you from a mistake, annotate it: `(last hit: YYYY-MM-DD)`.
> Prune entries not triggered in 60 days — they're either internalized or irrelevant.

## Rule: [Example] Never commit without running typecheck

**When:** Before any `git commit`

**Mistake:** Pushed code with TypeScript errors that broke CI (2024-01-15)

**Rule:** Always run `npm run typecheck` before committing. If it fails, fix before commit.

---

## Rule: [Example] Check existing code before creating new files

**When:** Adding new functionality

**Mistake:** Created a new utility function that already existed in `lib/utils.ts`

**Rule:** Search the codebase first (`grep` or `glob`) before creating new files or functions.

